        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 9:44AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 944 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
west of Decatur, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Gentry...                         Maysville...
Rogers...                         Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...
Highfill...                       Vaughn...
Monte Ne...                       Gravette...
Decatur...                        Cave Springs...
Bentonville...                    Hiwasse...
Pea Ridge...                      Healing Springs...
Springtown...                     Lowell...
Miller...                         Bella Vista...
Centerton...                      Rocky Comfort...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 76 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
